snippet.textDisplay: These singles that you guys keep releasing are absolutely amazing. Ronnie you never cease to amaze me I swear. With each of these singles you guys put out I have literally rushed to try and share the experience with my friends. I get just as much excitement from being able to share your music with others as I do from listening to it myself. Its like getting a brand new car and being thrilled to show all my friends. Also as a side note, I have just recently began trying to learn how to play the piano after wanting to learn for years and just bought my first keyboard a week ago. That being said when this song started and you were playing the piano it completely spiked my motivation further and now I want to teach myself how to play your song no matter how much practicing it takes me. Thanks for the great music! And as usual I already can't wait for your next song to drop!

snippet.textDisplay:
I was about to call this a masterpiece, but then it turned into screaming. Don't get me wrong, I'm a real metalhead and I'm digging screaming but til that moment I thought you guys really dared to do something. And you still did, but a pure ballad with some minor roughly vocals would really have been a paradigm shift.

Still... This is a great song, but I got the feeling that you feeled pressured to have this metal transition in it. And I just want to say that this should not have an influence.
Probably I got the wrong feeling and you guys just freakin wanted to do it... Then I'm sorry and it's definitely cool :D

I really love your songs, thank you for giving us some good music.
